{"履修期": "秋学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "The purpose of this course is to develop students' sociological perspective and their understand of societal systems by exploring human behavior, culture, social structures, and contemporary social issues. The aim is to familiarize students with critical thinking and its relationship to social change.&nbsp;", "到達目標": "1. Applying sociological perspectives to everyday life2. Understanding social structures, culture, human behavior, and change3. &nbsp;Analyzing social patterns, power dynamics, and diverse life experiences4. Observing how race, glass, gender, ethnicity, culture, religion, and other factors create diverse social experiences5. Recognizing how identities are socially created6. Developing the tools to become a more engaged and well-informed participant and member of today's complex global society7. Practicing (hands-on) intercultural communication strategies to better interact with people from different social, religious, and cultural values", "特記事項": "【合併】Sociology in English Ｃ（社会学部）/Sociology in English Ｃ（社会学部）", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "1. This course will be conducted in English only and English will be the means of communication between the students and the instructor. (Students will also be expected to communicate with one another in English.)2. Students are encouraged to actively participate in class discussions, both independently and collaboratively.3. This is unique course that explores a global perspective by offering students the opportunity to engage in a cultural exchange experience with students from a university in Malaysia. Through a combination of synchronous and asynchronous sessions, students will interactively discuss and collaborate on projects and activities with visiting students.&nbsp;4. For this particular course, KGU is collaborating with UTAR (Universiti Tunku Abdul Rahman) in Malaysia. Students from UTAR will spend one week at KGU's campus in mid-October and during this time, 